Spring Break in New Jersey

When school’s out, you’ll find that New Jersey has no shortage of fun things to do with kids throughout the state.

Learn More

10 Ways to Love Spring in New Jersey

Make the most of the season with this quick bucket list of must-try experiences.

Learn More

2019 Park Passes Available Now!

If you are a frequent visitor to the state parks, the purchase of the annual pass can mean a substantial savings over the payment of daily walk-in or parking fees.

Learn More

Horseback Riding at Island Beach State Park

Six miles of ocean beach in the southern and central portions of the park are available for equestrian use from October 1 through April 30.

Learn More

2019 Open Enrollment is over. Still need health insurance?

You can enroll in or change plans if you have certain life changes, or qualify for NJ Family Care (Medicaid)

Learn More

Jersey Fresh Products

Find out what’s available in New Jersey by month and learn more about each product.

Distracted driving is any activity that could divert a person’s attention away from the primary task of driving.

The April 1 tour of 5 New Jersey locations will bring attention to the importance of the Census.

Join Us

The State Park Service is seeking lifeguards to staff 14 swim areas around the state. No experience necessary, we train and provide USLA certification!
